exercises.expected_solution:
Error at startup:
  Caused by: org.hibernate.MappingException:
  Column 'street' is duplicated in mapping for entity 'Shipment'

Reason: Both pickupAddress and deliveryAddress embed Address with the
  SAME column names (street, city, pincode, state). A table cannot
  have two columns named 'street'.

Fix — use @AttributeOverrides to rename delivery columns:

@Entity
public class Shipment {
    @Id String id;

    @Embedded  // columns: street, city, pincode, state
    private Address pickupAddress;

    @Embedded
    @AttributeOverrides({
        @AttributeOverride(name="street",  column=@Column(name="delivery_street")),
        @AttributeOverride(name="city",    column=@Column(name="delivery_city")),
        @AttributeOverride(name="pincode", column=@Column(name="delivery_pincode")),
        @AttributeOverride(name="state",   column=@Column(name="delivery_state"))
    })
    private Address deliveryAddress;  // columns: delivery_street, delivery_city, etc.
}

